org.jscsi.target.settings
Class NumericalValueRange

java.lang.Object
  org.jscsi.target.settings.NumericalValue
      org.jscsi.target.settings.NumericalValueRange

public final class NumericalValueRange
extends NumericalValue

This is a NumericalValue sub-class for representing integer intervals. Each NumericalValueRange is defined by two integers - min and max - the lower and the upper bound of the represented interval.

Author:
Andreas Ergenzinger

Method Detail

create

public static final NumericalValueRange create(int min,
                                               int max)
The build method for creating NumericalValueRange objects. The specified min and max parameters are going to be used for initializing the min and max variables of the new NumericalValueRange. Since this only makes sense if min ≤ max, null will be returned if this requirement is violated.

Parameters:
min - the lower bound
max - the upper bound
Returns:
a NumericalValueRange representing the specified interval or null

parseNumericalValueRange

public static final NumericalValueRange parseNumericalValueRange(String value)
Parses a NumericalValueRange from a String. The lower and boundaries must be separated by a '~' character and the the leading integer must not be larger than the trailing one. If these format requirements are violated the method will return null.

Parameters:
value - the String to parse
Returns:
a NumericalValueRange representing the interval in the parsed String or null
